Algorithm:
1. Start.
2. Input the size of the array n.
3. Declare an array arr of size n.
4. Input the elements of the array.
5. Initialize a variable largest with the first element of the array (arr[0]).
6. For each element arr[i] from index 1 to n-1:
If arr[i] > largest, update largest = arr[i].
7. After the loop, largest contains the largest number in the array.
8. Print the value of largest.
9. Stop.

Pseudocode:
START
PRINT "Enter the size of the array:"
INPUT n
DECLARE array arr[n]
PRINT "Enter the elements of the array:"
FOR i = 0 TO n-1 DO
    INPUT arr[i]
END FOR

SET largest = arr[0]
FOR i = 1 TO n-1 DO
    IF arr[i] > largest THEN
        largest = arr[i]
    ENDIF
END FOR

PRINT "The largest number is:", largest
STOP
